#Text=1. Introduction
#Text=Most plants have evolved a range of defense systems to protect themselves when they are infected by insects .
#Text=Constitutive and inducible secondary metabolites may increase after being fed upon by insects to prevent further damage .
#Text=Metabolites that were induced in damaged plants could prove useful for preventing and controlling insects .
#Text=Some extracts from plants can inhibit growth of Spodoptera litura Fab . larvae or kill them .
#Text=Asarum ichangense is a species of the genus Asarum .
#Text=Yi et al. reported that all parts of A. sieboldii caused 100 % mortality in both Lycoriella ingenua and Coboldia fuscipes larvae .
#Text=Essential oil from A. sieboldii was toxic to the house dust mite Dermatophagoide sfarina .

#Text=It was determined that a type of neolignane asatone and isoasatone was reported from the genus Asarum , and that asatone has proved to be a potent antifeedant to papilionid butterfly , Luehdorfia puziloi larvae .
#Text=Asatone and isoasatone A have seldom been investigated for its toxicity to caterpillars , such as S. litura .
#Text=S. litura is a harmful insect which is widespread in many countries , as it causes significant damage to crops every year .
#Text=It feeds on 181 plant species that belong to 39 families , which include maize ( Zea mays ) , sunflower ( Helianthus annuus ) , sorghum ( Sorghum bicolor ) , and chickpea ( Cicer arietinum ) .
#Text=Many secondary metabolites demonstrate a number of different mechanisms to control pests .

#Text=For example , quercetin negatively affected the mid-gut of S. litura from Euphorbia hirta L , and flavonoids , ginkgolide , and bilobalide from Ginkgo biloba inhibit the metabolic enzymes in Hyphantria cunea larvae by glutathione transferases ( GSTs ) , acetylcholinesterase ( AChE ) , carboxylesterase ( CarE ) , and mixed-functional oxidase ( MFO ) .
#Text=Insect cytochrome P450 monooxygenases ( P450s ) are well-known for their roles in the oxidative metabolism of xenobiotics such as insecticides and plant allelochemicals in pest insects .
#Text=They have been divided into four clades : CYP2 , CYP3 , CYP4 , and the mitochondrial CYP clade .
#Text=The clade CYP3 is further subdivided into different CYP families .
#Text=The CYP321A , CYP6B , and CYP9A subfamilies play a role in the metabolism of xenobiotics and insecticide resistance .

#Text=The products of P450-mediated reactions ( phase I reactions ) can be metabolized by phase II enzymes , such as GSTs , which lead to the production of hydrophilic compounds that can be excreted by phase III transporters .
#Text=Here , we report that asatone and isoasatone A analyzed from A. ichangense can be potential defensive compounds against S. litura .
#Text=The anti-insect mechanisms of both compounds are described using mid-gut histopathology , P450s , GSTs , and AChE of S. litura .
